        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@V1OL3TF0X I am sorry, I have forgot to mention, that every `app` in `apps` folders has also a `package.json`, so the `root_dir` function will set to `app1`, when I am editing a file in `app1`, as there is the closest `package.json`. I guess this is the related issue as well https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/issues/3818#issuecomment-2848836794\n\n```\n├── apps/\n│   ├── app1/\n│   │   ├── src/\n│   │   ├── vite.config.ts\n│   │   └── package.json\n│   └── app2/\n│       ├── src/\n│       ├── vite.config.ts\n│       └── package.json\n├── node_modules/\n├── package.json\n├── vite.config.ts\n└── oxlint.config.ts\n```\n\nFor now I have set `root_dir` in my config to this to overcome this.\n\n```lua\nroot_dir = function(bufnr, on_dir)\n\tlocal cmd = \"oxlint\"\n\tlocal fname = vim.api.nvim_buf_get_name(bufnr)\n\n\tlocal root_markers = require(\"lspconfig.util\").insert_package_json(\n\t\t{ \".oxlintrc.json\", \".oxlintrc.jsonc\", \"oxlint.config.ts\" },\n\t\t{ \"oxlint\", \"vite%-plus\" },\n\t\tfname\n\t)\n\n\troot_markers = require(\"lspconfig.util\").root_markers_with_field(\n\t\troot_markers,\n\t\t{ \"vite.config.ts\" },\n\t\t\"vite%-plus\",\n\t\tfname\n\t)\n\n\tlocal dirs = vim.fs.find(root_markers, { path = fname, upward = true, limit = 3 })\n\n\tlocal root_dir = vim.fs.dirname(dirs[1])\n\tlocal local_cmd = vim.fs.joinpath(root_dir, \"node_modules/.bin\", cmd)\n\n\tif vim.fn.executable(local_cmd) == 1 then\n\t\ton_dir(root_dir)\n\t\treturn\n\tend\n\n\tfor i = 2, #dirs do\n\t\tlocal dirname = vim.fs.dirname(dirs[i])\n\t\tlocal_cmd = vim.fs.joinpath(dirname, \"node_modules/.bin\", cmd)\n\n\t\tif vim.fn.executable(local_cmd) == 1 then\n\t\t\troot_dir = dirname\n\t\t\tbreak\n\t\tend\n\tend\n\n\ton_dir(root_dir)\nend\n```",
